urnals, and the poetry of George Herbert and Robert Herrick, all of which Huebert carefully analyses in order to illuminate the dynamic and emergent nature of early modern privacy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticismyEarly modern, 1500-1700. 0aPrivacy in literature. 7aDRAMA / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266952940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442669529423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442669529.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles